08/06/2007
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Police have arrested a Macedonian citizen for making alleged threats against US President George W. 
Bush, who arrives in Sofia on Sunday (June 10th) for a two-day visit. 
Interior Minister Rumen Petkov says the man sent threatening messages via the internet. 
He declined to comment on how serious they were. 
(bTV, News.bg, BNR, Darik, Makfax - 07/06/07)
